        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em><strong>Sentinel</strong>:&nbsp;15th level</em></p>\n<p>When you are subjected to an effect that forces you to make a saving throw, you can spend 2 force points to add your Wisdom or Charisma modifier (your choice, minimum of one) to the saving throw if doesn&rsquo;t already include that modifier. If you do so, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw, and only half damage if you fail. You can wait until after you roll the d20 to use this feature, but you must decide before the GM says it succeeds or fails.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>If the GM uses save roll automation they may wish to tweak the rules for this feature.</p>\n</section>",
